<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
VENTURA TEACHER NAMED TO STATE POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dorothy J. Lee, a fifth-grade teacher at the Will Rogers Elementary School in 
Ventura, was appointed Tuesday to the State Board of Education by Gov. George 
Deukmejian. 
</P>
<P>
Lee, 55, has taught in the Ventura Unified School District for more than 30 
years. 
</P>
<P>
She will replace the late Elias S. Manolakas, a school board member who died 
last December. 
</P>
<P>
Pending confirmation of her appointment to the 11-member board by the state 
Senate, Lee will serve the remainder of Manolakas' four-year term, which 
expires in January, 1992. 
</P>
<P>
Lee, a resident of Ventura, received an undergraduate degree in industrial 
relations from UC Berkeley and a master's degree in educational administration 
from USC. 
</P>
<P>
She is married to Harry Lee and they have a son, Roderick. 
</P>
</TEXT>
