<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SIMI VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
SCHOOL BOARD HEARS TECHNOLOGY REPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JONATHON GAME 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Educators heard a preliminary report Tuesday on a study of technology in the 
classroom, including electronic chalkboards, interactive videos and 
computer-assisted instruction. 
</P>
<P>
Simi Valley Unified School District Supt. 
</P>
<P>
John W. Duncan told board members that the committee which is undertaking the 
study was created to assess the district's need for improved information and 
technology systems. 
</P>
<P>
A 27-member task force is interviewing 133 teachers, administrators, district 
employees, students and community members. Each of the people interviewed is 
asked to complete a survey on information technology and its usefulness to the 
district. 
</P>
<P>
The group will develop a long-range technology plan for the district, Duncan 
said. Assisting are a number of IBM consultants whose services have been 
donated to the district. 
</P>
<P>
The final report is due Aug. 7. JONATHON GAME 
</P>
</TEXT>
