<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 2 MEN CRITICALLY INJURED IN FIGHT NEAR CITY 
HALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men standing nearly toe to toe in downtown Los Angeles shot and stabbed 
each other about 6 p.m. Tuesday in a parking lot across from City Hall, leaving 
both assailants hospitalized in critical condition, police said. 
</P>
<P>
"It was sort of like the Old West," said Sgt. David Torres. 
</P>
<P>
The two unidentified men started arguing at 1st and Main streets, and one 
pulled a gun and the other a knife, Torres said. The gunman fired three to five 
shots while the man with the knife stabbed his opponent in return, the sergeant 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Police in a patrol car heard the shots and ended the bloody exchange. 
</P>
</TEXT>
