<HEADLINE>
<P>
LINDA VISTA SCHOOL GETS $550,555 GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Linda Vista Elementary School in San Diego will receive $550,555 as one of 15 
schools in eight states awarded major grants by the RJR Nabisco Foundation to 
help improve education in America. 
</P>
<P>
The San Diego school board invited Linda Vista teachers to make a presentation 
to trustees later this month on their plans to spend the money, which is the 
largest private grant to a single school in the district's history. 
</P>
<P>
Linda Vista, with a heavily Indochinese and Latino student population, has 
implemented its own academic program that emphasizes English language study and 
native-language instruction in basic subjects in the morning, followed by 
afternoon enrichment in art or music. 
</P>
</TEXT>
