<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: VINCENT, GOP GROUP EACH FINED $16,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Inglewood Mayor Edward Vincent and the treasurer of a California Young 
Republicans group have each been fined $16,000 for violations of the state Fair 
Political Practices Act. 
</P>
<P>
Vincent was fined by the Fair Political Practices Commissions for eight 
campaign disclosure violations in an April, 1987, election. Vincent earlier had 
agreed to to the settlement arrangement with the FPPC. 
</P>
<P>
The other $16,000 fine involved eight campaign reporting violations against the 
California Young Republicans Political Action Committee and its treasurer, 
Daniel Dellicompagni of Huntington Beach. The FPPC said the organization failed 
to file six semi-annual campaign statements and two pre-election campaign 
statements by the deadlines in the last four years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
