<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: EL CAJON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 6-year-old kindergartner suffered massive head injuries Tuesday after he ran 
into a street and was struck by a car near Bostonia Elementary School in El 
Cajon, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Kyle B. Davis was flown to Children's Hospital, where he was on a life-support 
system, a hospital supervisor said. 
</P>
<P>
Davis and a friend were waiting to be picked up about 11:25 a.m. at Grape 
Street and Broadway when he ran north on Broadway toward his school, police 
spokeswoman Sheri Naumann said. He was run over by a 1984 Toyota pickup truck 
driven by Todd Higgens, 25, of El Cajon, Naumann said. 
</P>
<P>
Higgens was not held and police are investigating. 
</P>
</TEXT>
