<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In other baseball games: 
</P>
<P>
Saugus 4, Ridgecrest Burroughs 2 -- With the score tied, 2-2, Saugus (9-2-1, 
6-0) scored two runs in the sixth when John Albert walked with the bases loaded 
and Chris Hernandez hit a sacrifice fly in a game at Saugus. 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley 6, Canyon 4 -- David Cooke had three hits, scored a run and 
drove in another as the visiting Antelopes (3-8, 2-4) upset second-place Canyon 
(6-5, 3-3) in a Golden League game. 
</P>
<P>
Palmdale 9, Quartz Hill 3 -- Jim Carson (4-1) scattered seven hits and walked 
none, and Jim Ortega had three hits and three runs batted in for host Palmdale 
(8-3, 4-2) in a Golden League game. 
</P>
<P>
Hart 4, Alhambra 0 -- R. J. Simone's first-inning grand slam held up for 
first-place Hart (9-1-2, 6-0) in a Foothill League game at Hart. 
</P>
<P>
Junior right-hander Keith Halcovich (2-1) and senior left-hander Andrew 
Lorraine combined on a one-hitter. 
</P>
<P>
St. John Bosco 18, Alemany 9 -- St. John Bosco scored nine runs on five walks, 
four hits and two errors in the seventh inning of a Del Rey League game at 
Alemany. Joey Rosselli drove in four runs with a double and triple for Alemany 
(7-8, 2-4). 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Newbury Park 3, Westlake 0 -- Senior Lea Lopez threw a perfect game, striking 
out 14 of the 21 batters, to lead Newbury Park to a Marmonte League win at 
Westlake. 
</P>
<P>
It was Lopez's second career no-hitter and first perfect game. 
</P>
