<P>
KORS, SEAHAWKS REACH AGREEMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVEN HERBERT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former El Camino Real High football standout R. J. Kors has agreed to a 
two-year contract with the Seattle Seahawks, his agent, Paul Bartelt, announced 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Kors, 23, a safety, also played at Taft College and Cal State Long Beach. 
Seattle drafted him in 1989 but released him in the preseason. STEVEN HERBERT 
</P>
