<P>
Schering-Plough Sells Maybelline: Schering-Plough Corp., seeking to disentangle 
itself from the financially unpredictable beauty-products business, agreed to 
sell its Maybelline unit for $300 million to a group including the unit's 
management and Playtex Family Products Corp. Maybelline was placed on the 
auction block in December, as Madison, N.J.-based Schering-Plough was forced to 
bow to the fierce competitive forces shaping the global pharmaceutical 
business. 
