<P>
MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gone in 15 Minutes?Two Andy Warhol silk-screen prints were stolen from an 
exhibit of paintings, sculptures and other works of modern art in Tokyo, police 
said Tuesday. Warhol's "Paramount" and "The New Spirit," reportedly worth 
$144,000 apiece, were reported stolen at the Tokyo International Trade Center 
at Harumi. Naoyuki Nagayama of Nippon Bijutsu Shuppan, the sponsor of the 
five-day exhibition which ended Monday, said the prints were in their places 
when sponsors checked before closing Sunday.. BETH KLEID 
</P>
