</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Say Innocent: Actor John Cusack, star of the movie "Say Anything," pleaded 
innocent Tuesday in Beverly Hills to two drunken-driving charges stemming from 
a collision with another vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
Because the charge is a misdemeanor, Cusack, 23, of Beverly Hills, was not 
required to be in court for his arraignment. Instead, he entered his plea 
through his attorney, Michael Chaney. Cusack, who remains without bail, faces a 
May 4 pretrial hearing. BETH KLEID 
</P>
