<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MOTA, SHORT POWER FULLERTON'S VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gary Mota and Jim Short hit solo home runs to help Fullerton College break a 
six-game losing streak with a 7-4 victory over Saddleback in an Orange Empire 
Conference baseball game Tuesday at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff Manship added two hits and two RBIs for Fullerton (17-9, 8-6 in 
conference). 
</P>
<P>
Steve Trachsel (7-2) allowed only one earned run over nine innings for the 
victory. Buster Nietzke had four hits for Saddleback (3-12, 9-15). 
</P>
<P>
In other Orange Empire Conference baseball games: 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago 7, Cypress 3 -- Matt Lackie (8-2) pitched 6 1/3 innings for the 
victory for first-place Rancho Santiago (23-5, 12-3). Marty Neff had four hits 
with three runs and Conrad Colby hit a solo home run. 
</P>
<P>
Doug McConathy had three hits, including a home run and a triple and is nine of 
his last 15. Jason Bates had three hits for Cypress (16-13, 5-9). 
</P>
<P>
Golden West 9, Riverside 8 -- Gerad Cawhorn walked with the bases loaded in the 
eighth to break an 8-8 tie for host Golden West. Jon Orcher had four hits 
including a two-run home run that gave Golden West a 5-0 lead in the second 
inning. 
</P>
<P>
Frank Herman had three hits and Cawhorn had two hits and three RBIs for 
second-place Golden West (19-6, 10-5). 
</P>
