<TEXT>
<P>
BOATS: Landlocked Costa Mesa was a major California center for boat building 
until soaring property values and environmental regulations pushed the industry 
out. . . . But many boats still are made in the county (D5). On display when 
the Anaheim Boat Show opens today: "Boat in a Bag," an inflatable contained in 
a sack. Its manufacturer, Elco Marine of Santa Ana, says it's used mostly for 
pulling water skiers. Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
