ambush a year ago, is up for sale. . . . The 35 1/2-acre spread was owned by 
flamboyant former Highway Patrol officer Horace (Big Mac) McKenna, who tried to 
buy the Mustang Club topless bar in Santa Ana before he was murdered at the 
ranch's entrance. Asking price: $2.5 million. . . . Real estate agent Fred 
Davis says most prospective buyers have been aware of the ranch's history but 
were not mere curiosity-seekers. . . . Brea police say the case remains under 
investigation. "We're plugging away at it," Detective Grant Gulickson said. 
