Ill., 6-1, 6-2 today in a second-round match. Maleeva, ranked 10th in the world 
and seeded fifth in this event, had a first-round bye, and Harvey-Wild easily 
won her opening match 6-0, 6-1 over Hellas Ter Riet. 
</P>
<P>
Jennifer Capriati was scheduled to play a second-round match later today 
against Angeliki Kanellopoulou of Greece. 
</P>
<P>
Navratilova said her toughest competition this time is "my next round. I can 
have stiff competition from a lot of people. A lot of players are good on this 
stuff, and they play on it more than I do." 
